WEBVTT

00:01.880 --> 00:03.210
Previously on Scandal...

00:03.210 --> 00:04.420
Meg: No one's even thinking
about Jenny.

00:04.420 --> 00:05.580
Her killer
could be anyone.

00:05.580 --> 00:07.000
Jake: Olivia Pope,
Jennifer Fields.

00:07.000 --> 00:08.330
You are going to kill
Francisco Vargas

00:08.330 --> 00:10.460
when he takes the stage
tomorrow night.

00:11.040 --> 00:13.000
Sandra, all of this --
all of this is over now.

00:13.000 --> 00:14.460
I got you.

00:14.460 --> 00:16.000
You put a gun to the head
of the woman I love,

00:16.000 --> 00:17.710
and I belong to you?!

00:17.710 --> 00:19.080
You're wondering whether
you actually have a choice.

00:21.500 --> 00:23.960
Wherever your daughter goes,
we have eyes on her.

00:23.960 --> 00:25.330
You have a second chance

00:25.330 --> 00:27.170
Survival of the fittest,
Olivia.

00:27.170 --> 00:28.710
Are you a client
or a friend?

00:31.500 --> 00:35.790
[ Sugarhill Gang's
"Rappers Delight" plays ]

00:35.790 --> 00:38.500
[ Both grunting ]

00:38.500 --> 00:40.080
That's some weak tea,
Hucky.

00:40.080 --> 00:41.920
Uh, Hucky?
What'd you teach me?

00:41.920 --> 00:43.880
The only punch that counts

00:43.880 --> 00:45.670
is the punch
you don't see coming.

00:45.670 --> 00:48.540
[ Grunting ]

00:48.540 --> 00:50.670
♪ I said the hip hop,
the hippie the hippie ♪
[ Exhales sharply ]

00:50.670 --> 00:51.960
♪ To the hip, hip hop,
and you don't stop ♪
[ Both breathing heavily ]

00:51.960 --> 00:53.500
♪ The rock it
to the bang bang boogie ♪

00:53.500 --> 00:55.170
♪ Say, up jump the boogie ♪
Come on, get up.

00:55.170 --> 00:56.710
♪ To the rhythm of the boogie,
the beat ♪
Get up!

00:56.710 --> 00:58.330
♪ Now what you hear
is not a test ♪
Good girl.

00:58.330 --> 00:59.670
♪ I'm a-rappin' to the beat ♪
Today's lesson is

00:59.670 --> 01:01.380
don't ever stay down
and don't ever relax.

01:01.380 --> 01:03.420
♪ And me, the groove,
and my friends ♪
Don't ever relax?

01:03.420 --> 01:05.750
♪ Are gonna try
to move your feet ♪
You taught me that
last week.

01:05.750 --> 01:08.830
♪ See, I am Wonder Mike,
and I'd like to say hello ♪

01:08.830 --> 01:10.580
[ Both breathing heavily ]

01:10.580 --> 01:11.880
♪ To the black, to the white,
the red and the brown ♪

01:11.880 --> 01:13.330
♪ The purple and yellow ♪

01:13.330 --> 01:14.620
♪ But first I gotta ♪

01:14.620 --> 01:16.540
♪ Bang bang,
the boogie to the boogie ♪

01:16.540 --> 01:18.620
♪ Say up jump the boogie
to the bang bang boogie ♪

01:18.620 --> 01:19.880
♪ Let's rock ♪

01:19.880 --> 01:21.540
♪ You don't stop ♪
Quinn: Huck!

01:21.540 --> 01:23.710
What are you doing here?

01:23.710 --> 01:25.170
Looking for you!
You're not answering your phone!

01:25.170 --> 01:26.460
I turned it off.

01:26.460 --> 01:28.000
Which is why
I had to hack your geotags

01:28.000 --> 01:28.790
to track you down.

01:29.620 --> 01:30.750
I know you.

01:30.750 --> 01:32.380
What's the emergency?

01:32.380 --> 01:33.620
Boss lady's missing.

01:33.620 --> 01:34.960
Quinn was supposed to meet Liv
back at the office

01:34.960 --> 01:36.670
after Jake and Vanessa
went to the Liberty Report,

01:36.670 --> 01:38.460
but...
I can't find her.
Anywhere.

01:38.460 --> 01:40.170
Her car's still
in the parking garage.

01:40.170 --> 01:41.620
She's not
answering her phone.

01:41.620 --> 01:43.580
She's obviously not with you
because you're doing whatever.

01:43.580 --> 01:45.330
Liv's gone, Huck.

01:45.920 --> 01:47.000
Hi!

01:49.620 --> 01:50.710
Oh, Meg!

01:50.710 --> 01:51.710
Am I right?

01:51.710 --> 01:53.380
That's me.

01:53.380 --> 01:55.250
You're
Jenny's best friend.

01:55.250 --> 01:56.500
I was.

01:56.500 --> 01:57.620
Charlie: Who?

01:57.620 --> 01:59.040
You know,
Jenny from the campaign.

01:59.040 --> 02:00.250
From the voicemail --
Jenny.

02:00.250 --> 02:01.710
Wait, was Jenny that chick

02:01.710 --> 02:03.250
with the burnt-up hand
you chopped up?
Charlie.

02:03.250 --> 02:05.830
Oh, Jenny, Jenny,
right!

02:05.830 --> 02:08.210
Meg, nice to meet you.

02:08.210 --> 02:10.000
Sorry for your loss.
Charlie?

02:10.000 --> 02:11.420
What,
that was a nice thing to say.

02:11.420 --> 02:13.620
I got to go.
Go? Where?

02:13.620 --> 02:14.830
Did Liv leave you
a message?

02:14.830 --> 02:16.080
I'm sorry that
I got to cut this short.

02:16.080 --> 02:17.210
Quinn:
Did Liv say where she is?

02:17.210 --> 02:18.580
Is everything okay?

02:18.580 --> 02:19.960
I hope so.

02:22.330 --> 02:23.290
Okay.

02:23.880 --> 02:25.250
Huck.

02:29.380 --> 02:32.210
Here, so we can see each other
whenever we want.

02:32.210 --> 02:33.540
♪ 'Cause I'm guaranteed
to make you rock ♪

02:33.540 --> 02:34.670
I'd like that.

02:34.670 --> 02:36.170
♪ I said one, two,
three, four ♪

02:36.170 --> 02:38.170
♪ Tell me, Wonder Mike,
what are you waitin' for? ♪

02:38.170 --> 02:40.540
♪ To the hip hop,
the hippie to the hippie ♪

02:40.540 --> 02:42.330
♪ The hip, hip a-hop,
and you don't stop ♪

02:42.330 --> 02:43.670
♪ The rock it
to the bang bang boogie ♪

02:43.670 --> 02:45.000
♪ Say up jump the boogie ♪

02:45.000 --> 02:46.120
♪ To the rhythm of the boogie,
the beat ♪

02:46.120 --> 02:46.920
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

03:10.580 --> 03:11.920
Okay, let's go.

03:14.750 --> 03:17.040
[ Sniffles ]
I have a favor to ask.

03:17.040 --> 03:18.880
Get in the car, Liv,
come on.

03:18.880 --> 03:20.710
I need you
to do something for me.

03:22.170 --> 03:24.120
They still here?
Is who still here?

03:24.120 --> 03:25.290
The men
who brought you here.

03:25.290 --> 03:26.290
How many are there?

03:26.290 --> 03:28.080
I walked here
in these stupid shoes.

03:28.080 --> 03:29.880
I need you
to do something for me.

03:29.880 --> 03:31.790
Did they hurt you
or make you do something --?

03:31.790 --> 03:34.080
Huck! Shut up.
I'm fine.

03:34.080 --> 03:35.710
I'm asking you
for something.

03:35.710 --> 03:37.330
I need you
to do something for me,

03:37.330 --> 03:38.790
and you're not
listening to me.

03:38.790 --> 03:40.120
What?

03:42.670 --> 03:43.960
I need you
to kill Rowan.

03:49.750 --> 03:51.460
[ Sniffles ]

03:53.170 --> 03:56.420
I want my father dead,
and I need you to do it.

04:17.170 --> 04:20.330
Olivia:
[ Breathing shallowly ]

04:20.330 --> 04:22.330
Huck:
You should sit down.
I should've known.

04:22.330 --> 04:23.710
Sit down.
It's who he is.

04:23.710 --> 04:25.790
Liv...
He wanted me
in the Oval.

04:25.790 --> 04:27.620
He was gonna put me there
no matter what it took.
Liv...

04:27.620 --> 04:29.540
My father killed the President
of the United States of America.

04:29.540 --> 04:31.000
I'm not going to sit down.

04:31.000 --> 04:32.250
Who told you
it was your father?

04:32.250 --> 04:33.880
It doesn't matter.
It matters.

04:33.880 --> 04:36.540
Huck.
You asked me
to kill him.

04:36.540 --> 04:38.420
You asked me
to kill Command.

04:38.420 --> 04:39.830
It matters.

04:39.830 --> 04:41.000
Who told you it was him?

04:41.000 --> 04:43.040
Jake. Jake told me.

04:44.120 --> 04:45.880
Jennifer Fields,
Olivia Pope.

04:45.880 --> 04:47.670
Olivia Pope,
Jennifer Fields.

04:47.670 --> 04:49.330
Olivia: She's alive.

04:49.330 --> 04:50.750
And according to her,

04:50.750 --> 04:53.040
my father
made her leave that message.

04:53.040 --> 04:55.750
It was Cyrus Beene.

04:55.750 --> 04:57.620
He killed Frankie Vargas.

04:57.620 --> 05:00.830
And then my father
ordered Jake to kill her.

05:00.830 --> 05:02.710
It's time for you to take
what's yours, son.

05:02.710 --> 05:03.580
It's time to come home.

05:03.580 --> 05:05.460
But Jake didn't kill her.

05:05.460 --> 05:06.830
Because she's
an innocent victim.

05:06.830 --> 05:08.380
Well, that's never been
a problem for Jake.

05:08.380 --> 05:10.710
Jake believes my father
might have some bigger plan,

05:10.710 --> 05:12.620
and that Jennifer could be
the key to figuring it out.

05:12.620 --> 05:14.080
Huck:
What? And you don't?

05:14.080 --> 05:15.540
I don't think
there's anything bigger

05:15.540 --> 05:16.460
than killing
the President.

05:16.460 --> 05:18.460
Whoa, maybe he didn't.

05:18.460 --> 05:20.250
Why are you going
out of your way to
defend my father?

05:20.250 --> 05:22.880
Command always put
the Republic first.

05:22.880 --> 05:25.080
Killing Frankie --
Frankie was good.

05:25.080 --> 05:28.330
Killing Frankie is not
putting the Republic first.

05:28.330 --> 05:30.830
Something about this
feels off.

05:30.830 --> 05:33.460
My father killed
Frankie Vargas!

05:36.210 --> 05:39.460
[ Breathing shallowly ]

05:39.460 --> 05:41.670
Huck...

05:41.670 --> 05:44.670
If I could ask anyone else

05:44.670 --> 05:46.380
to do what needs to be done,
I would.

05:46.380 --> 05:50.040
But you are the only person
I can trust.

05:50.040 --> 05:52.960
You are asking me
to kill your father.

05:54.960 --> 05:55.750
Yes.

05:58.460 --> 05:59.620
Do you know what happened

05:59.620 --> 06:00.920
the last time
you asked me to do that?

06:00.920 --> 06:02.120
Yes!

06:02.120 --> 06:04.920
I peeled an innocent man's skin
from his body

06:04.920 --> 06:06.790
with a razor blade.
Huck --

06:06.790 --> 06:09.080
I just want you to know
what you're asking me to do.

06:09.080 --> 06:10.290
He killed the President.

06:10.290 --> 06:12.670
I know
what I'm asking you to do!

06:12.670 --> 06:15.000
You have to be sure,
Liv.

06:15.000 --> 06:21.330
You have to be sure --
100 percent!

06:21.330 --> 06:23.670
If you
are absolutely sure...

06:26.830 --> 06:28.500
...yeah.

06:28.500 --> 06:31.670
For you, I'll do it.

06:35.500 --> 06:37.710
I'm sure.

06:37.710 --> 06:40.750
♪♪

07:02.210 --> 07:04.080
[ Cabinet doors close ]

07:11.580 --> 07:12.790
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

07:12.790 --> 07:15.580
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

07:16.750 --> 07:17.830
[ Horn honks in distance ]

07:28.170 --> 07:29.250
[ Gun clicks ]

07:36.120 --> 07:38.920
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

07:41.080 --> 07:42.580
[ Car door closes ]

07:45.960 --> 07:47.460
[ Horn honks ]

07:50.620 --> 07:55.750
[ Man speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

07:57.670 --> 08:00.330
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:04.500 --> 08:07.580
Woman: Next stop,
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

08:11.080 --> 08:12.710
Man: Please stand clear
of the train doors.

08:12.710 --> 08:14.540
All passengers...

08:14.540 --> 08:17.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:27.540 --> 08:28.580
Rowan: Let it go.

08:30.120 --> 08:33.500
[ Chime sounds ]

08:33.500 --> 08:34.540
Man: Doors closing.

08:36.290 --> 08:39.080
[ Horn honks ]

08:39.080 --> 08:40.000
I'm not armed.

08:44.250 --> 08:46.380
That makes it easier, then.

08:46.380 --> 08:47.960
2 minutes and 15 seconds.

08:47.960 --> 08:49.420
What?

08:49.420 --> 08:50.790
You have
2 minutes and 12 seconds

08:50.790 --> 08:51.790
until they're back.

08:51.790 --> 08:53.210
Who?
The people following me.

08:53.210 --> 08:54.460
No one's following you.

08:54.460 --> 08:55.460
You're using up your time!

08:55.460 --> 08:56.880
What do you want to know?

08:56.880 --> 08:58.670
I didn't come here
to ask questions.

08:58.670 --> 09:00.120
No, you came here
to kill me.

09:00.120 --> 09:01.880
She sent you here
to kill me!

09:01.880 --> 09:03.960
But that's not gonna happen,
so use your time wisely.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.580
Did you do it?
Yes!

09:05.580 --> 09:07.750
Then this is
going to happen.

09:07.750 --> 09:10.080
Do you want to know
why I did it?

09:10.080 --> 09:11.120
I know why.

09:11.120 --> 09:12.620
To get her elected --

09:12.620 --> 09:13.580
that's what she told you,
right?

09:14.880 --> 09:15.960
Right?

09:15.960 --> 09:17.750
That is not why.

09:17.750 --> 09:20.330
45 seconds.

09:20.330 --> 09:21.580
Why?

09:21.580 --> 09:23.710
I had no other choice!
What?

09:23.710 --> 09:25.670
You're saying these people
who are following you

09:25.670 --> 09:27.710
forced you to do it?
I am.

09:27.710 --> 09:30.040
Nobody forces you
to do anything.
Exactly.

09:30.040 --> 09:31.290
Nobody.

09:31.290 --> 09:32.670
Nobody forces me.

09:32.670 --> 09:34.460
This is somebody.

09:34.460 --> 09:37.750
Pay attention, soldier,
because it is happening now.

09:37.750 --> 09:38.790
It is on.

09:38.790 --> 09:40.620
We are living in
interesting times.

09:40.620 --> 09:41.880
This is not a test.

09:41.880 --> 09:44.500
Our adversary
is more than worthy,

09:44.500 --> 09:46.210
fully armed
and fully funded,

09:46.210 --> 09:49.120
smart, cold, cruel!

09:49.120 --> 09:52.460
They don't care to play by
the civilized rules of war.

09:52.460 --> 09:55.290
Animals -- they had me!

09:55.290 --> 09:56.790
I was given no choice.

09:56.790 --> 09:59.500
You killed the President
of the United States.

09:59.500 --> 10:01.170
To save the life
of a woman that I loved.

10:01.170 --> 10:02.250
They threatened her.

10:02.250 --> 10:03.620
They said
that they would kill her.

10:03.620 --> 10:04.920
These people --
I believed them.

10:04.920 --> 10:06.580
What would you do
in that situation?

10:06.580 --> 10:07.620
It doesn't matter.
It does!

10:07.620 --> 10:09.000
I'm not asking you
a hypothetical!

10:10.420 --> 10:12.210
What are you
talking about?

10:12.210 --> 10:14.290
These people
are threatening Olivia,

10:14.290 --> 10:16.790
right now as we speak.

10:16.790 --> 10:18.210
You're lying.

10:18.210 --> 10:20.080
If I don't do
what these people want,

10:20.080 --> 10:21.210
they will kill Olivia.

10:21.210 --> 10:22.830
If I die,
they will kill Olivia.

10:22.830 --> 10:25.540
So what you decide here
matters very much,

10:25.540 --> 10:28.290
because you are
in the same position as me.

10:28.290 --> 10:31.120
Olivia's life
is in your hands!

10:31.120 --> 10:33.250
You're lying!

10:33.250 --> 10:35.080
Then why haven't you
shot me?

10:35.080 --> 10:36.750
Why didn't
I just shoot you?

10:36.750 --> 10:38.750
What is the point
of this lie?

10:38.750 --> 10:40.790
In 15 seconds,
a train is gonna pull up

10:40.790 --> 10:42.750
on that side
of the platform.

10:42.750 --> 10:44.540
A woman --
white, ponytail, orange coat --

10:44.540 --> 10:46.420
will get off
with a man in a suit

10:46.420 --> 10:47.750
with a scar
on his forehead.

10:47.750 --> 10:49.830
They will look around,
looking for me.

10:49.830 --> 10:52.420
And when they do not see me,
they will be very unhappy.

10:52.420 --> 10:53.920
Woman: Train arriving.

10:53.920 --> 10:56.460
Please stand clear
of the platform exit.

10:56.460 --> 10:58.380
[ Train approaching ]

11:00.000 --> 11:03.040
♪♪

11:14.380 --> 11:15.540
Next stop...

11:15.540 --> 11:18.120
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

11:18.120 --> 11:20.040
Man: Watch the closing doors,
please.

11:20.040 --> 11:22.080
[ Chime dings ]

11:22.080 --> 11:24.580
[ Train door closes ]

11:36.670 --> 11:37.790
[ Elevator bell dings ]

11:41.580 --> 11:44.120
Man: Northeast Regional Train
265 to Boston

11:44.120 --> 11:45.790
will be boarding in 10 minutes.

11:45.790 --> 11:48.420
Northeast Regional Train 265
for Boston

11:48.420 --> 11:49.790
will be boarding
in 10 minutes.

11:51.920 --> 11:53.120
Who are they?
Rowan: I don't know.

11:53.120 --> 11:54.920
All I know is
whoever is watching Olivia

11:54.920 --> 11:57.420
is close to her --

11:57.420 --> 11:59.670
in her circle,
on the inside,

11:59.670 --> 12:02.170
a traitor among us.

12:02.170 --> 12:05.290
You need to find out
who it is,

12:05.290 --> 12:06.290
because I can't.

12:06.290 --> 12:07.500
I'm trapped.

12:11.210 --> 12:14.210
Will you help me?

12:14.210 --> 12:15.710
Can you do that?

12:18.830 --> 12:21.380
A traitor among us --

12:21.380 --> 12:22.790
trust no one.

12:22.790 --> 12:25.880
♪♪

12:25.880 --> 12:28.750
[ Man speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

12:28.750 --> 12:32.000
♪♪

12:32.000 --> 12:35.040
♪♪

13:01.960 --> 13:05.000
♪♪

13:22.580 --> 13:23.500
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

13:26.120 --> 13:28.120
[ Computer beeps ]

13:28.120 --> 13:29.750
[ Keyboard clacking ]

13:29.750 --> 13:31.960
[ Computer beeping ]

13:31.960 --> 13:33.420
Quinn: [ Distorted ]
You're supposed to be covering

13:33.420 --> 13:35.670
that transition meeting
in an hour, Charlie.

13:35.670 --> 13:37.210
If you lost the notes --
Charlie: [ Distorted ]
I didn't lose the notes.

13:37.210 --> 13:38.960
They're here. Somewhere.

13:38.960 --> 13:41.080
Maybe if you weren't busy
stalking a dude online

13:41.080 --> 13:44.250
to get ahold of some weird,
endangered Indian elephant --

13:44.250 --> 13:46.330
Not "weird," Robin.
"Awesome."

13:46.330 --> 13:48.710
Imagine me riding
in on that bad boy
at the wedding.

13:48.710 --> 13:50.830
No way in hell
is that happening.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.620
No endangered species
at the wedding.

13:52.620 --> 13:53.830
Fine.
Then pitch something else.

13:53.830 --> 13:56.080
I'm serious.

13:56.080 --> 13:57.460
Have an idea instead of
me having all of them.

13:57.460 --> 13:59.080
Hey, I have ideas.

13:59.080 --> 14:00.670
But the only idea you've had

14:00.670 --> 14:02.210
was postponing
until after the inauguration.

14:02.210 --> 14:03.750
I'm talking the fun stuff,

14:03.750 --> 14:05.500
like shooting rats
between dinner courses.

14:05.500 --> 14:06.330
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

14:06.330 --> 14:08.420
Ah, see? My notes.

14:08.420 --> 14:09.750
Right where I left them.

14:09.750 --> 14:15.330
[ Distorted voices
speaking indistinctly ]

14:15.330 --> 14:16.580
What do you think of Meg?

14:16.580 --> 14:18.210
Like,
speaking of rats, or --

14:18.210 --> 14:19.670
She seem
a little slow to you,

14:19.670 --> 14:21.120
like not all there
or something?

14:21.120 --> 14:22.960
You talked to her
for all of five seconds.

14:22.960 --> 14:24.330
Yeah,
and I could already tell.

14:24.330 --> 14:26.790
She's a total rando psycho.

14:26.790 --> 14:28.880
God, you'd think Huck would
have some higher standards,

14:28.880 --> 14:30.580
but I guess
that's just his thing.

14:30.580 --> 14:32.380
Rando psychos.
[ Mocking cat meow ]

14:32.380 --> 14:34.170
Hey, don't do that.

14:34.170 --> 14:35.880
Don't make cat noises
just because a woman says

14:35.880 --> 14:37.710
she doesn't like
another woman.

14:37.710 --> 14:39.080
I'm just saying --
you sound kind of
jealous of her.

14:39.080 --> 14:41.170
[ Scoffs ] Jealous?

14:41.170 --> 14:42.250
[ Laughing ] Of what?

14:42.250 --> 14:44.670
That basic 2004 pixie cut?

14:44.670 --> 14:46.670
[ Scoffs ] I didn't mean
"jealous" jealous.

14:46.670 --> 14:47.920
Okay, then,
how the hell did you mean it?

14:47.920 --> 14:50.540
You're beautiful.
What?

14:50.540 --> 14:51.830
I don't think
I told you that today.

14:51.830 --> 14:54.120
Out! Leave.

14:54.120 --> 14:55.420
Okay,
is this one of those times

14:55.420 --> 14:56.620
where you say to leave,
but you really mean --

14:56.620 --> 14:58.830
Get out of here, Charlie!
Now!

14:58.830 --> 15:01.290
Okay, okay, don't...
[ Sighs ] Oh, God.

15:06.000 --> 15:08.540
I'm alone. Yes.

15:08.540 --> 15:09.670
Have you found a place
to put Jennifer?

15:12.120 --> 15:14.080
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

15:24.250 --> 15:25.500
Don't move.

15:25.500 --> 15:27.250
Huck,
what are you doing?

15:31.830 --> 15:33.330
Rowan was right.

15:33.330 --> 15:34.790
We do have a mole.

15:34.790 --> 15:37.250
♪♪

15:37.250 --> 15:38.750
It's nice to finally meet you,
Jennifer.

15:38.750 --> 15:40.500
I've heard
a lot of good things.
Who is he?

15:40.500 --> 15:41.790
Jennifer,
you should wait for us

15:41.790 --> 15:43.540
in the next room
while we talk.

15:43.540 --> 15:44.830
Jennifer,
stay right where you are.

15:44.830 --> 15:49.710
♪♪

15:49.710 --> 15:50.540
In here.

15:50.540 --> 15:54.750
♪♪

15:54.750 --> 15:56.380
Keep low, just in case.

15:56.380 --> 15:58.670
[ Door closes ]

15:58.670 --> 15:59.880
Are you crazy?

15:59.880 --> 16:00.960
Start talking.

16:03.420 --> 16:04.830
Quinn agreed to help me

16:04.830 --> 16:06.170
get to the bottom of whatever's
going on with Rowan.

16:06.170 --> 16:07.330
I thought about calling you,

16:07.330 --> 16:09.080
but you would have
ratted me out to Olivia,

16:09.080 --> 16:10.500
and the last time I saw her,

16:10.500 --> 16:11.960
she wasn't exactly
being open-minded.

16:11.960 --> 16:14.250
Not exactly open-minded?

16:14.250 --> 16:16.620
On the phone,
you said she went bonkers.

16:16.620 --> 16:18.250
Looks like
she's not the only one.

16:18.250 --> 16:19.830
She's in danger.

16:19.830 --> 16:21.460
Someone forced Rowan
to kill Frankie

16:21.460 --> 16:23.420
by threatening
a person close to him.

16:23.420 --> 16:26.080
Rowan says these same people
placed a mole by Liv's side.

16:26.080 --> 16:27.830
All they have to do
is say a word,

16:27.830 --> 16:28.920
and she's dead.

16:28.920 --> 16:30.880
And you think
one of us is the mole?

16:30.880 --> 16:32.580
Not you.

16:32.580 --> 16:34.670
You or Charlie.

16:34.670 --> 16:37.170
I am not a --

16:37.170 --> 16:40.830
Wait a minute.
Rowan says?

16:40.830 --> 16:44.750
I am not a mole, Huck.

16:44.750 --> 16:46.000
[ Scoffs ]

16:46.000 --> 16:47.750
In fact, the only double-agent
I see here is you.

16:50.420 --> 16:53.080
Anything else
you want to admit, Huck?

16:53.080 --> 16:54.670
Huh? Huh?

16:54.670 --> 16:56.250
Now's your chance.

16:56.250 --> 16:57.920
The person
these people threatened --

16:57.920 --> 16:59.170
did Rowan say
who they were?

16:59.170 --> 17:01.290
It's a woman.
That's all I know.

17:02.330 --> 17:03.420
I think I know
who she is.

17:08.580 --> 17:09.620
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
Sandra Potter --

17:09.620 --> 17:10.960
she's an old friend
of Rowan's.

17:10.960 --> 17:12.710
They seem to have reconnected
recently.

17:12.710 --> 17:14.620
They were spending
a lot of time together
before election day.

17:14.620 --> 17:18.040
Since,
no sign of her anywhere.

17:18.040 --> 17:19.790
This means Rowan
could be telling the truth.

17:19.790 --> 17:21.000
Or playing us hard.

17:23.920 --> 17:25.420
I'll get on this.
We'll track her down.

17:25.420 --> 17:27.210
You let me know
as soon as you find something.

17:27.210 --> 17:30.000
♪♪

17:38.750 --> 17:41.120
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

17:41.120 --> 17:44.120
[ Keyboard clacking ]

17:52.710 --> 17:54.330
Are you gonna apologize?

17:54.330 --> 17:57.040
For what?
For thinking
for a second

17:57.040 --> 17:58.920
that I'm capable
of killing Olivia.

17:58.920 --> 18:00.380
I'm not sorry
for doing my job.

18:03.670 --> 18:05.420
I assume you've cleared Meg,
then?

18:05.420 --> 18:06.670
Meg?

18:06.670 --> 18:07.830
You two meet,

18:07.830 --> 18:09.670
she finds an excuse
to keep seeing you,

18:09.670 --> 18:11.960
things move quickly,
you give her a key.

18:11.960 --> 18:13.750
Meg reads books
about math.

18:13.750 --> 18:15.170
She...
[ Scoffs ]

18:15.170 --> 18:17.080
...squeezes my arm
during horror movies.

18:17.080 --> 18:18.670
She's still on Pinterest.
Mm-hmm.

18:18.670 --> 18:20.620
She's not a mole...

18:20.620 --> 18:21.830
or a rando psycho.

18:24.380 --> 18:25.620
You bugged me?

18:25.620 --> 18:27.170
I had to. There's a...

18:27.170 --> 18:28.080
Mole.

18:28.080 --> 18:30.380
Yeah, I've heard.

18:30.380 --> 18:31.670
Well, it's not Charlie,
so...

18:31.670 --> 18:33.080
But Charlie's a mercenary.

18:33.080 --> 18:35.830
Charlie's my fiancé.

18:35.830 --> 18:37.460
First thing I did
was shut that crap down.

18:37.460 --> 18:38.790
He doesn't even
go to the bathroom

18:38.790 --> 18:39.920
without
asking for permission first.

18:39.920 --> 18:41.000
Trust me.

18:44.380 --> 18:46.000
[ Sighs ]

18:46.420 --> 18:47.750
You know...

18:47.750 --> 18:50.790
you and I haven't really
talked in a while.

18:50.790 --> 18:52.710
And I haven't been around
like I used to be.
[ Sighs heavily ]

18:52.710 --> 18:54.460
What's your point?

18:54.460 --> 18:56.380
I don't know --
if you're mad about it...

18:56.380 --> 18:57.540
I'm not mad.

18:57.540 --> 18:59.170
Hmm?

18:59.170 --> 19:01.500
Or jealous,
if that's what you're thinking.

19:01.500 --> 19:04.500
[ Laughs ]
I'm surprised, Huck.

19:04.500 --> 19:05.960
[ Chuckles ]

19:05.960 --> 19:08.000
You still haven't
learned your lesson?

19:09.330 --> 19:10.670
What's that
supposed to mean?

19:10.670 --> 19:11.460
You know
what that means.

19:13.290 --> 19:14.170
What, Becky?

19:15.830 --> 19:16.920
Meg's not Becky.

19:16.920 --> 19:18.170
Yeah,
Becky wasn't Becky

19:18.170 --> 19:19.960
until she left you
holding the gun

19:19.960 --> 19:21.920
that shot the President
in the head.

19:24.290 --> 19:25.960
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:25.960 --> 19:28.420
Look, I -- I really hope
I'm wrong, Huck.

19:29.290 --> 19:31.000
Yeah, well, you are.

19:44.580 --> 19:46.210
There you are!

19:46.210 --> 19:48.830
I had no idea you worked
so many late nights.

19:48.830 --> 19:50.250
That's got to be tough.

19:50.250 --> 19:51.290
What are you doing here?

19:52.170 --> 19:53.500
Oh, my God.

19:53.500 --> 19:55.380
This isn't cool.

19:55.380 --> 19:56.250
Cool?

19:56.250 --> 19:58.290
Me, staying here,

19:58.290 --> 19:59.580
coming over unannounced.

19:59.580 --> 20:00.960
I -- I'm so sorry.

20:00.960 --> 20:02.710
I thought that a key
meant that...

20:02.710 --> 20:04.750
Oh, my God.

20:04.750 --> 20:05.920
We should've
talked about it more.

20:05.920 --> 20:07.250
Meg, it's okay.
Boundaries --

20:07.250 --> 20:08.710
We should of maybe
set some boundaries.
Meg...

20:08.710 --> 20:10.830
I'm glad that you're here.

20:10.830 --> 20:12.920
I gave you a key
for a reason.

20:12.920 --> 20:15.040
Just, I forgot, is all.

20:17.330 --> 20:18.330
Okay.

20:18.330 --> 20:19.500
Okay?

20:23.080 --> 20:25.330
♪ Hip hop,
the hippie, the hippie ♪

20:25.330 --> 20:27.380
♪ To the hip, hip hop,
and you don't stop ♪

20:27.380 --> 20:29.420
♪ A-rock it out, Baby Bubba,
to the boogie da bang bang ♪

20:29.420 --> 20:31.880
♪ The boogie to the boogie,
the beat ♪

20:31.880 --> 20:33.750
♪ I said I can't wait
till the end of the week ♪

20:33.750 --> 20:36.040
♪ When I'm rappin' to the rhythm
of a groovy beat ♪

20:36.040 --> 20:38.210
♪ And attempt to raise
your body heat ♪

20:38.210 --> 20:40.080
♪ Just blow your mind too,
so that you can't speak ♪

20:40.080 --> 20:42.540
♪ And do a thing but a rock
and shuffle your feet ♪

20:42.540 --> 20:44.540
♪ And let it change up to
a dance called the freak ♪

20:44.540 --> 20:46.790
♪ And when you finally do
come into your rhythmic beat ♪

20:46.790 --> 20:48.790
♪ Rest a little while
so you don't get weak ♪

20:48.790 --> 20:50.920
♪ I know a man named Hank ♪

20:50.920 --> 20:53.210
♪ He has more rhymes
than a serious bank ♪
Huck?

20:53.210 --> 20:55.540
♪ So come on Hank,
sing that song ♪
I wanted to ask you...

20:55.540 --> 20:56.920
♪ To the rhythm of the boogie,
the bang bang da bong ♪

20:56.920 --> 20:59.750
...about your boss,
Olivia.

21:02.120 --> 21:03.580
What about her?

21:05.500 --> 21:07.460
She gets answers, right?

21:07.460 --> 21:13.250
Helps out the underdog,
takes on lost causes?

21:13.250 --> 21:16.250
Look, I don't want to put you
in an uncomfortable position,

21:16.250 --> 21:19.710
but we still don't know
who killed Jenny.

21:19.710 --> 21:20.880
And if Tom Larsen
didn't do it,

21:20.880 --> 21:22.250
then I still
don't really know

21:22.250 --> 21:23.460
what happened
to my best friend.

21:23.460 --> 21:26.380
And, I can't just --

21:26.380 --> 21:30.540
I can't just move on
like the rest of the country.

21:30.540 --> 21:33.170
So...

21:33.170 --> 21:35.080
I want Olivia's help.

21:36.500 --> 21:38.830
Do you think she'd help?

21:38.830 --> 21:40.830
To help you find
Jenny's real killer?

21:40.830 --> 21:42.080
She deserves justice

21:42.080 --> 21:44.290
just as much as
Frankie Vargas does,

21:44.290 --> 21:45.790
doesn't she?

21:45.790 --> 21:48.290
Maybe it's pointless.

21:48.290 --> 21:51.170
I don't know.

21:51.170 --> 21:54.170
I just thought I'd ask.

21:54.170 --> 21:55.880
No, you're right.

21:55.880 --> 21:57.750
I'll, um --
I'll talk to her for you.

21:59.380 --> 22:00.790
Would you mind
if I talked to her myself?

22:02.830 --> 22:05.420
As in face-to-face?

22:05.420 --> 22:07.250
Just you and Liv?

22:07.250 --> 22:09.000
For Jenny.

22:09.000 --> 22:12.500
I feel like I have to do this
on my own.

22:12.500 --> 22:14.830
Would that be weird?

22:18.620 --> 22:21.380
I'll see
if she's open to it.

22:21.380 --> 22:23.500
Really?

22:23.500 --> 22:27.330
Huck, that'd be amazing.

22:27.330 --> 22:29.120
[ Chuckles ]

22:29.120 --> 22:30.790
♪♪

22:36.830 --> 22:38.120
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

22:38.120 --> 22:40.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:45.000 --> 22:46.830
He's fine.

22:53.420 --> 22:56.080
There's a high-level inmate
I need your help getting to.

22:56.080 --> 22:58.460
You should ask Olivia.
I can't ask Olivia.

22:58.460 --> 22:59.460
I would love to help,
but --

22:59.460 --> 23:01.080
What if I had
something to trade,

23:01.080 --> 23:02.670
something you wanted?
Huck...

23:02.670 --> 23:04.040
Jennifer Fields is alive.

23:05.380 --> 23:07.170
Say that again?

23:07.170 --> 23:10.120
Jennifer Fields,
the woman from the cabin --

23:10.120 --> 23:11.750
she's alive.

23:11.750 --> 23:13.420
What's the name
of your inmate?

23:13.420 --> 23:15.210
[ Buzzer sounds ]

23:15.210 --> 23:17.380
[ Door opens ]

23:17.380 --> 23:20.250
Abby didn't tell me
what this is about,

23:20.250 --> 23:23.790
which isn't unusual.

23:23.790 --> 23:26.790
But, I have to ask.

23:26.790 --> 23:28.290
No, you don't.

23:28.290 --> 23:32.790
♪♪

23:32.790 --> 23:35.080
[ Buzzer sounds, door opens ]

23:35.080 --> 23:37.880
♪♪

23:42.170 --> 23:43.790
Hi, Becky.

23:43.790 --> 23:46.040
Hey, Huck.

23:47.580 --> 23:49.120
You look terrible.

23:49.120 --> 23:50.420
I've been better.

23:52.000 --> 23:54.080
Guess it's what
I should've expected.

23:54.080 --> 23:56.830
You wouldn't have come to see me
after all these years

23:56.830 --> 23:58.710
if everything was all good,
now would you?

23:58.710 --> 24:00.080
How'd you play me?

24:00.080 --> 24:01.710
What?

24:01.710 --> 24:03.170
You did something
when we were together.

24:03.170 --> 24:04.670
You figured out
something --

24:04.670 --> 24:07.380
a weakness, a blind spot.

24:07.380 --> 24:08.710
What was it?

24:08.710 --> 24:10.670
Well, this is new.

24:10.670 --> 24:13.540
How'd you get inside my head,
Becky?

24:13.540 --> 24:14.830
Or, do I need
to call you Kate?

24:15.750 --> 24:16.710
You weren't kidding

24:16.710 --> 24:18.670
when you said
you've been better, huh?

24:21.290 --> 24:23.670
All right, you want my help,
I want yours.

24:23.670 --> 24:25.670
What does that mean?

24:25.670 --> 24:27.750
I want to see my sister.

24:27.750 --> 24:29.380
I didn't know
you had a sister.

24:29.380 --> 24:31.620
She's dying.

24:33.580 --> 24:34.920
Maybe she's already dead.
I don't even know.

24:34.920 --> 24:38.620
It's impossible
to get information in here.

24:38.620 --> 24:40.750
I know she was diagnosed
two months ago

24:40.750 --> 24:42.830
with stage-four
pancreatic cancer.

24:42.830 --> 24:46.960
I spoke to her once.

24:46.960 --> 24:49.380
I know they'll never
let me out to see her,

24:49.380 --> 24:51.790
and she's in no condition
to come here,

24:51.790 --> 24:53.620
but maybe you could
go see her

24:53.620 --> 24:55.750
and just take a picture of her
for me.

24:55.750 --> 24:58.290
I don't even have
a picture of her.

25:00.080 --> 25:04.500
I think I can remember
what she looks like --

25:04.500 --> 25:07.830
scar on her right eyebrow,
freckles on her cheek.

25:07.830 --> 25:10.210
[ Sighs ]

25:10.210 --> 25:11.750
She had these big ears

25:11.750 --> 25:14.080
that would've looked stupid
on anybody else,

25:14.080 --> 25:15.620
but on her,
they were perfect.

25:17.210 --> 25:19.880
She was soft and warm
and perfect.

25:19.880 --> 25:21.750
She was -- is.

25:21.750 --> 25:23.750
She is my little baby sister

25:23.750 --> 25:27.000
and my best friend
and a beautiful girl,

25:27.000 --> 25:30.000
and I just want to see her face
one more time.

25:33.830 --> 25:35.960
I'm sorry.

25:35.960 --> 25:38.210
I can help you.

25:38.210 --> 25:40.040
I will help you.

25:42.210 --> 25:43.960
I just helped you.

25:45.040 --> 25:46.040
What?

25:46.040 --> 25:47.830
You are so gullible.

25:49.710 --> 25:51.080
That was a lie?

25:51.080 --> 25:52.580
[ Laughs ]
Yes, of course!

25:52.580 --> 25:54.040
Well, I have a sister,
but she's horrible.

25:54.040 --> 25:55.670
I honestly can't stand
the sight of her.

25:55.670 --> 25:57.460
[ Scoffs ]
Why would you do that?

25:57.460 --> 25:58.880
You asked me
how I played you.

25:58.880 --> 26:00.000
This is how I played you.

26:01.170 --> 26:03.040
You know, for as scary
as you look,

26:03.040 --> 26:05.250
you sure do have a soft spot
for a sob story.

26:09.000 --> 26:10.540
Who's playing you now?

26:10.540 --> 26:12.920
What's her name?

26:12.920 --> 26:14.460
No one.
No one?

26:16.460 --> 26:17.750
So, is she acting

26:17.750 --> 26:22.750
all sad and damaged
all the time?

26:22.750 --> 26:24.250
Is she?

26:24.250 --> 26:26.540
Her best friend died,
and she's scared.

26:26.540 --> 26:27.620
Bait and hook.

26:27.620 --> 26:28.710
No.
Yes.

26:28.710 --> 26:29.960
You're as gullible
as you ever were.

26:29.960 --> 26:31.500
I'm not.
You are.

26:31.500 --> 26:33.500
No!

26:33.500 --> 26:36.960
No, that was -- no.

26:36.960 --> 26:40.290
What you just did,
that was you.

26:40.290 --> 26:42.170
That was your trick.

26:42.170 --> 26:43.960
You're the one
who hasn't changed --

26:43.960 --> 26:46.920
not me, you!

26:46.920 --> 26:48.460
You.

26:52.420 --> 26:54.380
Aw, Huck, don't go.

26:54.380 --> 26:56.120
[ Pounds on door ]
[ Buzzer sounds ]

26:56.120 --> 26:57.710
This is the most entertainment
I've had in months.
[ Door opens ]

26:57.710 --> 26:59.580
♪♪

26:59.580 --> 27:01.670
Did you get
what you needed?

27:04.080 --> 27:06.080
Kind of thought
that might be the answer.

27:06.080 --> 27:06.960
[ Buzzer sounds ]

27:06.960 --> 27:07.880
♪♪

27:21.620 --> 27:24.920
[ Cellphone beeps ]

27:24.920 --> 27:25.960
[ Sighs ]

27:25.960 --> 27:28.120
[ Cellphone ringing ]

27:28.790 --> 27:31.880
[ Sighs ]
[ Cellphone beeps ]

27:31.880 --> 27:34.000
Did you do it?
Tell me it's done.

27:34.000 --> 27:35.420
There's a girl -- some woman
your father was seeing.

27:35.420 --> 27:36.790
Did you know that?

27:36.790 --> 27:38.460
What -- what --
what are you talking about?

27:38.460 --> 27:40.580
Sandra something.

27:40.580 --> 27:42.250
It's why he did
what he did.

27:42.250 --> 27:43.170
It was for her.

27:43.170 --> 27:44.920
He was protecting her.

27:44.920 --> 27:46.420
Huck,
I'm gonna need you to tell me

27:46.420 --> 27:47.120
what the hell is going on.

27:47.120 --> 27:49.120
I don't know exactly.

27:49.120 --> 27:51.170
I haven't gotten
that far yet.

27:51.170 --> 27:53.830
I just --
this is my theory.

27:53.830 --> 27:56.880
Okay, where is she,
this Sandra woman?

27:56.880 --> 27:58.420
I don't know.

27:58.420 --> 27:59.920
Huck, what do you know?

27:59.920 --> 28:03.500
I know your father
isn't the man he used to be.

28:03.500 --> 28:05.920
He's not this terrible person
anymore, Liv.

28:05.920 --> 28:07.540
He's -- he's in love.

28:07.540 --> 28:09.620
He's --
he's a different person now.

28:09.620 --> 28:10.750
He deserves a chance.

28:10.750 --> 28:11.960
I don't believe this.

28:11.960 --> 28:13.920
He's changed.
No!

28:13.920 --> 28:15.120
How can you be so sure?

28:15.120 --> 28:16.170
How can you not?

28:16.170 --> 28:17.540
He can't change, Huck.

28:17.540 --> 28:18.790
People can't change --

28:18.790 --> 28:20.420
not when they've spent
their entire lifetime

28:20.420 --> 28:21.540
doing the things
my father has done.

28:21.540 --> 28:22.420
He's a monster!

28:22.420 --> 28:24.210
There's no
getting over that.

28:24.210 --> 28:25.790
There's no
moving past that.

28:25.790 --> 28:27.830
There's no capacity
for change there!

28:27.830 --> 28:30.670
There's just him,
my father.

28:30.670 --> 28:33.380
He's been who he is
his entire life.

28:35.380 --> 28:36.790
If you can't do this,

28:36.790 --> 28:38.210
if you can't make it happen
by morning,

28:38.210 --> 28:39.880
I'm gonna need to find
someone who can.

28:39.880 --> 28:40.670
[ Cellphone beeps ]

28:57.880 --> 29:00.000
[ Engine starts ]

29:04.000 --> 29:07.040
♪♪

29:29.500 --> 29:30.750
[ Cellphone beeps ]

29:35.710 --> 29:36.920
What are you doing?

29:36.920 --> 29:39.710
♪♪

29:44.040 --> 29:47.460
Oh, that's good.

29:47.460 --> 29:50.420
You should come over,
celebrate.

29:50.420 --> 29:53.460
Yeah, I have news, too.

29:53.460 --> 29:55.920
Olivia agreed
to talk to you.

29:55.920 --> 29:58.790
She's gonna
take on Jenny's case.

29:58.790 --> 30:05.960
♪♪

30:05.960 --> 30:07.210
I'll see you then.

30:07.210 --> 30:09.170
♪♪

30:09.170 --> 30:10.170
[ Cellphone beeps ]

30:10.170 --> 30:13.210
♪♪

30:20.710 --> 30:22.170
[ Knock on door ]

30:27.380 --> 30:29.080
[ Knock on door ]

30:37.710 --> 30:40.710
Meg: Hey!

30:40.710 --> 30:41.830
So,
I don't think I have

30:41.830 --> 30:43.330
any money left
in my bank account,

30:43.330 --> 30:44.880
but this is
a bottle of champagne

30:44.880 --> 30:45.960
I can't pronounce,

30:45.960 --> 30:47.580
so it must be good.

30:49.710 --> 30:50.580
Oh!

30:51.620 --> 30:52.920
Mm.

30:52.920 --> 30:54.330
Huck: Mm.

30:55.500 --> 30:56.620
[ Exhales deeply ]
You feel good.

30:56.620 --> 30:57.790
So do you.

30:59.290 --> 31:00.960
You have any room
in the fridge?

31:00.960 --> 31:02.120
This wasn't chilled.

31:04.620 --> 31:06.250
Tell me more
about your day.

31:08.080 --> 31:09.710
I already told you.

31:09.710 --> 31:11.500
You got called
for an interview.

31:11.500 --> 31:12.920
Yeah.

31:12.920 --> 31:14.920
My day was fine,
I guess.

31:14.920 --> 31:18.330
I met with an old friend
I hadn't seen in ages.

31:18.330 --> 31:19.500
I don't have
many old friends.

31:19.500 --> 31:20.880
I don't like them.

31:20.880 --> 31:23.540
They're just a reminder
that you can never change.

31:23.540 --> 31:25.790
I disagree.

31:25.790 --> 31:29.710
I couldn't decide between
etorphine and methohexital.

31:32.540 --> 31:33.710
Huck...

31:33.710 --> 31:35.290
I chose etorphine.

31:35.290 --> 31:36.540
It's an opiate.

31:36.540 --> 31:38.460
The methohexital
would've made you feel like

31:38.460 --> 31:39.920
you were burning on the inside,

31:39.920 --> 31:41.330
and I didn't want that
for you.

31:41.330 --> 31:43.210
This is hard for me.

31:43.210 --> 31:47.330
I don't want to do this,
but you're making me do this.

31:48.420 --> 31:50.670
You can tell me now,

31:50.670 --> 31:52.880
or I can force it out of you
when you wake up.

31:52.880 --> 31:56.250
Who are you working for?

31:56.250 --> 31:57.830
My firm?

31:57.830 --> 31:59.880
The woman that you met with
at the park today --

31:59.880 --> 32:01.040
you were sitting
next to her!

32:01.040 --> 32:02.080
You were watching me.

32:02.080 --> 32:03.170
Who is she?

32:03.170 --> 32:04.540
Why are you following me?

32:04.540 --> 32:05.620
Who is she?!

32:05.620 --> 32:06.710
I don't know!

32:06.710 --> 32:08.540
What -- I...

32:08.540 --> 32:10.540
That's where
I take my lunch.

32:10.540 --> 32:13.500
She -- she came down and --
and she sat next to me,

32:13.500 --> 32:15.120
but I -- I don't even
remember her name.

32:15.120 --> 32:16.580
She said
she worked at my firm,

32:16.580 --> 32:18.420
but -- but I'd never
seen her before!

32:18.420 --> 32:19.960
I don't even
remember her name!

32:19.960 --> 32:21.290
You're lying.

32:21.290 --> 32:23.790
Helen? Hannah?

32:23.790 --> 32:25.210
I can't remember.

32:25.210 --> 32:26.250
[ Sighs ]

32:26.250 --> 32:28.210
I wish you'd make this
easier on me.

32:28.210 --> 32:32.710
You have no idea
how hard this is for me.

32:32.710 --> 32:35.080
I had never met
that woman before.

32:35.080 --> 32:37.040
I swear.

32:37.040 --> 32:39.540
It -- it was like she
was trying to be my
friend or something.

32:39.540 --> 32:40.830
We talked about, uh,

32:40.830 --> 32:43.120
a plant
that I have on my desk.

32:43.120 --> 32:44.460
What is this?

32:44.460 --> 32:45.580
I don't --

32:45.580 --> 32:47.500
[ Gasping ]

32:47.500 --> 32:48.620
No!

32:48.620 --> 32:51.380
[ Breathing shallowly ]

32:51.380 --> 32:54.120
I trusted you!
Aah!

32:54.120 --> 32:58.880
[ Crying ] I-I-I-I have no idea
who you think I am

32:58.880 --> 33:00.620
or what is going on.

33:00.620 --> 33:04.460
But please...

33:04.460 --> 33:08.170
Huck...don't do this.

33:08.170 --> 33:13.790
It was a mistake
to trust you.

33:13.790 --> 33:16.330
[ Breathing shallowly ]

33:16.330 --> 33:19.750
[ Sighs ]

33:19.750 --> 33:21.500
[ Normal voice ] Fine.

33:21.500 --> 33:22.750
Do it.

33:25.120 --> 33:26.540
Jam that crap into my neck

33:26.540 --> 33:30.580
and do whatever you're gonna do,
you monster.

33:30.580 --> 33:33.670
I don't know
who put this in your head,

33:33.670 --> 33:35.960
but you better
look into my eyes first.

33:35.960 --> 33:39.040
And if you see someone
who doesn't love you,

33:39.040 --> 33:41.580
who you can't trust,

33:41.580 --> 33:43.170
then go ahead.

33:45.250 --> 33:46.580
Go for it,

33:46.580 --> 33:49.290
whoever the hell you are!

33:49.290 --> 33:52.080
[ Breathing shallowly ]

33:59.380 --> 34:00.170
Go.

34:09.540 --> 34:11.080
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

34:11.080 --> 34:13.960
Huck:
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:13.960 --> 34:15.460
Uh, what's going on?

34:15.460 --> 34:17.580
When were you
gonna tell me?
Tell you?

34:17.580 --> 34:19.040
About your secret meetings
with my father,

34:19.040 --> 34:21.750
and this ridiculous theory

34:21.750 --> 34:23.380
that my father
killed Frankie Vargas

34:23.380 --> 34:25.000
because someone threatened
some old girlfriend of his.

34:25.000 --> 34:26.670
It's true, Liv.
Open it.

34:29.790 --> 34:33.040
Meet Sandra Potter,
my father's old girlfriend.

34:33.040 --> 34:34.080
Charlie:
Our old B613 dumpsite

34:34.080 --> 34:35.580
doesn't get a lot of use
these days,

34:35.580 --> 34:37.080
so she stuck out
like a sore thumb.

34:37.080 --> 34:38.420
This doesn't mean
anything.

34:38.420 --> 34:39.790
Anybody could've
killed her.

34:39.790 --> 34:42.000
This car was reported stolen
the day before the election --

34:42.000 --> 34:43.500
the day she died.

34:43.500 --> 34:44.750
Rowan's prints
are all over it.

34:44.750 --> 34:46.750
Olivia: Huck, my father
didn't save Sandra.

34:46.750 --> 34:47.420
He killed her.

34:47.420 --> 34:48.670
My guess is,

34:48.670 --> 34:50.210
she found out about
his assassination plan.

34:50.210 --> 34:52.210
And my father,
romantic that he is,

34:52.210 --> 34:54.750
put a bullet in her head
to shut her up.

34:54.750 --> 34:55.830
This doesn't make sense.

34:55.830 --> 34:57.500
He was telling the truth.
He was using you.

34:57.500 --> 34:58.830
No, he's not.

34:58.830 --> 35:01.080
He had people following him.

35:01.080 --> 35:02.420
Uh, I saw her --

35:02.420 --> 35:04.580
this blond woman
on the Metro...

35:04.580 --> 35:06.620
Blond woman on the D.C. Metro --
how'd he pull that off?

35:06.620 --> 35:09.080
You also thought there was
a mole inside of OPA.

35:09.080 --> 35:10.420
He got in your head, man.
It happens.

35:10.420 --> 35:12.330
He even thought it was me.
He put a gun to my head.

35:12.330 --> 35:15.210
Huck, my father was lying,
buying time.

35:15.210 --> 35:19.210
Your father was not lying,
and I am not crazy!

35:19.210 --> 35:22.670
There are people --
forces controlling him.

35:22.670 --> 35:25.380
No, there aren't.
There's just him.

35:25.380 --> 35:27.580
That's all there is,
that's all there ever is,

35:27.580 --> 35:28.830
time after time.

35:28.830 --> 35:31.000
You know that.
You're wrong.

35:31.000 --> 35:32.580
You're wrong.
He loved that woman.

35:32.580 --> 35:34.420
He was forced to do that!
Is this love?

35:34.420 --> 35:36.830
A bullet in the head,
being dumped in a junkyard?

35:36.830 --> 35:38.750
You're wrong.
Why should I believe you?

35:38.750 --> 35:40.380
Because I am right
and you are wrong!

35:40.380 --> 35:42.290
Because I am not the one
with the blind spot

35:42.290 --> 35:43.540
when it comes
to your father.

35:43.540 --> 35:45.120
That's you.

35:45.120 --> 35:47.000
You're the one
that's broken.

35:47.000 --> 35:48.540
That's you!
Enough!

35:50.620 --> 35:53.460
My father killed Frankie,
and he killed this woman,

35:53.460 --> 35:55.000
and he twisted your head.

35:55.000 --> 35:56.920
That is the truth.

35:56.920 --> 36:00.170
You're wrong.

36:00.170 --> 36:02.290
Maybe he used to be
a monster.

36:02.290 --> 36:04.750
Maybe he killed people.
Maybe he was awful.

36:04.750 --> 36:06.380
Maybe he was.

36:06.380 --> 36:08.750
But people change.

36:08.750 --> 36:10.790
People...change.

36:10.790 --> 36:13.960
It happens.

36:13.960 --> 36:16.460
Maybe they can meet, uh,
a nice woman

36:16.460 --> 36:19.170
and fall in love
and have a relationship,

36:19.170 --> 36:20.920
and be normal.

36:20.920 --> 36:25.120
People can change.

36:25.120 --> 36:27.080
You are wrong
about your father.

36:27.080 --> 36:29.420
So, no,
I'm not gonna kill the man

36:29.420 --> 36:31.670
who loves you most
in this world,

36:31.670 --> 36:34.040
even more than me.

36:34.040 --> 36:35.040
This?

36:35.040 --> 36:36.540
He did this for a reason.

36:36.540 --> 36:38.380
He's in pain.
He's a prisoner.

36:38.380 --> 36:40.040
Forgive him.

36:40.040 --> 36:42.790
Help him.
Do not kill him.

36:42.790 --> 36:46.000
I...am...right.

36:46.000 --> 36:47.920
I am right!

36:47.920 --> 36:49.330
You are wrong.

36:49.330 --> 36:56.880
♪♪

36:56.880 --> 36:59.790
Quinn, find my father,
finish the job.

36:59.790 --> 37:01.080
Huck,
get rid of the body.

37:04.830 --> 37:07.880
Huck: [ Grunting ]

37:20.380 --> 37:23.420
♪♪

37:50.330 --> 37:53.380
♪♪

37:58.920 --> 38:01.120
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

38:01.120 --> 38:03.920
♪♪

38:04.830 --> 38:06.380
[ Device beeps ]

38:06.380 --> 38:08.540
[ Computer beeps ]

38:08.540 --> 38:11.580
[ Keyboard clacking ]

38:15.920 --> 38:17.290
[ Computer beeps ]
Rowan: Incredible.

38:17.290 --> 38:18.210
Sandra. Honey,
you ain't seen nothin' yet!

38:18.210 --> 38:20.120
Rowan:
A Yangchuanosaurus.

38:20.120 --> 38:22.040
Sandra:
I've been working with a team,
assembled them myself.

38:22.040 --> 38:24.250
There's a private collector
paying the bill, Eli.

38:24.250 --> 38:25.250
[ Chuckles ]

38:25.250 --> 38:26.250
I could use a partner.

38:26.250 --> 38:28.120
Yes, I am in.

38:28.120 --> 38:29.670
I am in, baby!

38:29.670 --> 38:31.580
Sandra: What is this?
Rowan: A drink.

38:31.580 --> 38:33.830
A drink?
Well,
not just any drink.

38:33.830 --> 38:35.710
That was 40 years ago.

38:35.710 --> 38:38.120
Not a lot of time
in the scope of things.

38:38.120 --> 38:39.670
Man: Who exactly
is in charge here?

38:39.670 --> 38:41.670
Him?

38:41.670 --> 38:42.580
[ Gunshot ]

38:42.580 --> 38:44.750
Man: Now, I'm in charge.

38:44.750 --> 38:46.460
Rowan: You put a gun to the head
of the woman I love,

38:46.460 --> 38:48.500
and I belong to you?!

38:48.500 --> 38:50.170
Theodore: You have
a streak of weakness, Eli.

38:50.170 --> 38:51.330
We found it.

38:51.330 --> 38:52.880
Rowan: You people.

38:52.880 --> 38:58.080
Always thinking
you're better than us.

38:58.080 --> 39:00.170
[ Gunshot ]
[ Gasps ]

39:00.170 --> 39:01.920
[ Bill Withers'
"Lean on Me" plays ]
I have no weaknesses.

39:01.920 --> 39:04.080
No owns me!

39:04.080 --> 39:06.790
Woman:
Wherever your daughter goes,
we have eyes on her.

39:06.790 --> 39:09.460
And when I say "eyes," I mean
we have an actual human being

39:09.460 --> 39:11.290
who, within seconds
of hearing from me,

39:11.290 --> 39:13.040
can put a bullet
in your daughter's brain.

39:13.040 --> 39:14.670
[ Computer keyboard clacks ]

39:14.670 --> 39:17.670
♪ Mm, mm-mm, mm-mm ♪

39:17.670 --> 39:21.120
♪ Mm-mm, mm-mm ♪

39:21.120 --> 39:26.080
♪ Mm-mm-mm, mm, mm ♪

39:26.080 --> 39:29.330
♪ Sometimes in our lives ♪

39:29.330 --> 39:31.580
[ Cellphone beeps ]

39:31.580 --> 39:33.460
♪ We all have pain ♪

39:33.460 --> 39:34.830
Quinn, call it off.

39:34.830 --> 39:36.080
♪ We all have sorrow ♪
Stand down!

39:39.120 --> 39:40.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

39:40.460 --> 39:41.580
[ Knock at door ]

39:41.580 --> 39:43.380
♪ But if we are wise ♪

39:43.380 --> 39:45.170
Hi.

39:45.170 --> 39:47.210
♪ We know that there's ♪
Get him away from me.

39:47.210 --> 39:48.330
We need to talk to you.

39:48.330 --> 39:49.500
♪ Always tomorrow ♪
Talk to me?

39:49.500 --> 39:50.580
That man
almost murdered me!

39:50.580 --> 39:51.750
I tried to file a report

39:51.750 --> 39:53.330
and you know
what the police told me?

39:53.330 --> 39:54.670
♪ Lean on me ♪
That he doesn't
even exist!

39:54.670 --> 39:55.880
♪ When you're not strong ♪
So no, there's no way --

39:55.880 --> 39:57.620
Your friend Jennifer --
she's alive.

39:57.620 --> 39:59.420
♪ And I'll be your friend ♪
[ Gasps ]

40:00.920 --> 40:04.250
♪ I'll help you carry on ♪
Meg: This is insane!

40:04.250 --> 40:05.710
How --

40:05.710 --> 40:07.620
♪ For it won't be long ♪
Did you know she was alive?

40:07.620 --> 40:09.120
He couldn't tell you
for your own protection.

40:09.120 --> 40:12.080
How is sticking a needle
in my neck protecting me?

40:12.080 --> 40:13.250
♪ Till I'm gonna need ♪
He thought
you had been compromised.

40:13.250 --> 40:15.040
Meg: By who?
By the people
who want Jennifer dead.

40:15.040 --> 40:17.250
♪ Somebody to lean on ♪

40:17.250 --> 40:19.290
I can't ask you
to forgive him.

40:19.290 --> 40:21.380
♪ Please swallow your pride ♪
I won't do that.

40:21.380 --> 40:24.620
But I need him
to forgive himself.

40:24.620 --> 40:26.830
♪ If I have things ♪
I need that.

40:26.830 --> 40:30.380
♪ You need to borrow ♪
And I need your help.

40:31.620 --> 40:35.080
♪ For no one can fill ♪

40:35.080 --> 40:36.880
He loves you.

40:36.880 --> 40:38.120
♪ Those of your needs ♪
He's not a monster.

40:38.120 --> 40:39.710
He's not.

40:39.710 --> 40:41.420
♪ That you won't let show ♪
He's changed.

40:41.420 --> 40:43.250
People can change.

40:43.250 --> 40:46.750
♪ You just call on me,
brother ♪

40:46.750 --> 40:47.830
Look at me.

40:47.830 --> 40:49.380
♪ When you need a hand ♪

40:49.380 --> 40:50.830
Look at me!

40:50.830 --> 40:53.420
♪ We all need somebody ♪

40:53.420 --> 40:54.750
♪ To lean on ♪

40:54.750 --> 40:56.380
What happened to you?

40:56.380 --> 40:59.290
♪ I just might
have a problem ♪

40:59.290 --> 41:02.080
I promise.

41:02.080 --> 41:05.080
♪ That you'd understand ♪
I will never ever..

41:05.080 --> 41:07.500
♪ We all need somebody
to lean on ♪
...touch you again.

41:07.500 --> 41:08.960
I promise.

41:08.960 --> 41:10.920
♪ Lean on me ♪
Okay?

41:10.920 --> 41:14.580
♪ When you're not strong ♪

41:14.580 --> 41:17.710
♪ And I'll be your friend ♪

41:17.710 --> 41:19.960
♪ I'll help you carry on ♪

41:19.960 --> 41:21.460
We can only stay
for a little while.

41:21.460 --> 41:23.120
And, remember...
I know.

41:23.120 --> 41:25.120
♪ For it won't be long ♪
Jennifer's
really in there?

41:25.120 --> 41:27.380
...no one can know.

41:27.380 --> 41:28.710
♪ Till I'm gonna need ♪
Thank you, Huck.

41:30.710 --> 41:32.540
♪ Somebody to lean on ♪

41:32.540 --> 41:34.620
[ Door beeps, opens ]

41:34.620 --> 41:38.000
♪ You just call on me,
brother ♪

41:38.000 --> 41:40.250
♪ When you need a hand ♪
Oh, my God.

41:40.250 --> 41:41.250
[ Silenced gunshot ]

41:41.250 --> 41:42.620
♪ We all need ♪

41:42.620 --> 41:44.330
♪ Somebody ♪
[ Silence gunshot ]

41:44.330 --> 41:47.250
♪ To lean on ♪

41:47.250 --> 41:48.540
♪ I just might have
a problem ♪

41:48.540 --> 41:49.790
Is it done?

41:50.170 --> 41:52.040
It's done.

41:52.040 --> 41:54.000
♪ That you'd understand ♪
Jennifer Fields is dead.

41:54.000 --> 41:56.040
♪ We all need somebody ♪

41:56.040 --> 41:57.330
And Huck?

41:57.330 --> 42:00.000
♪ To lean on ♪

42:01.000 --> 42:04.000
♪ If there is a load ♪

42:04.000 --> 42:05.540
[ Silenced gunshot ]

42:05.540 --> 42:08.830
♪ You have to bear ♪

42:08.830 --> 42:13.500
♪ That you can't carry ♪

42:13.500 --> 42:15.170
♪ I'm right up your road ♪
Don't worry, Ms. Whelan.

42:15.170 --> 42:17.540
He'll have no idea
you were a part of this.

42:17.540 --> 42:21.210
♪ I'll share your load ♪

42:21.210 --> 42:22.460
[ Silenced gunshot ]

42:22.460 --> 42:26.210
♪ If you just call me ♪

42:26.210 --> 42:28.330
♪ Call me ♪

42:28.330 --> 42:29.540
♪ If you need a friend ♪

42:29.540 --> 42:31.420
♪ Call me ♪

42:31.420 --> 42:32.710
♪ Call me, uh-huh ♪

42:32.710 --> 42:35.040
♪ Call me ♪

42:35.040 --> 42:37.380
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

42:42.000 --> 42:45.040
♪♪
